page.title: 02Callington Carpark
page.content: In Callington carpark, it is not Pay and Display so it free. The carpark is right next to{Callington Primary {School.}At the bottom of it there is a way to go in and a way to go out, called the Entrance and Exit, and you must use them properly. At the top there is a Scout Headquaters. In front of it is some builders materials and a Dingy which is usually there, unless it is being used. Behind the hut there is a cricket field and to one side of it there is a road leading to some houses. In front of the hut with the dinghy there are some removal vans. Out of the carpark on one side is some farming machines. On the other side of there is our school and by the fenceing is some yellow lines which were laid down when it was re-surfaced. In the carpark there are 130 spaces.
